@startuml
title GPU Data Center Allocation & Model Serving Workflow

|AI Engineer / Data Scientist|
start
:Request Compute Resources (Full GPU or MIG Partition);

|Orchestration Layer (K8s & GPU-Operator)|
:Evaluate Cluster Capacity (H100/MI300X);
if (Resources Available?) then (Yes)
  :Allocate Compute Node via GPU-Operator;
  :Configure 400Gbps InfiniBand/RoCE Fabric;
else (No)
  :Queue Request;
  stop
endif

|Storage Layer (NVMe/SSD/S3)|
fork
  :Mount NVMe "Hot" Tier for Model Weights;
fork again
  :Connect to S3-Compatible API;
  :Verify Dataset Versioning & Lineage;
end fork
:Enable AES-256 Encryption at Rest;

|Model Registry & Inference Engine|
:Fetch Model from Centralized Registry;
:Select Quantization Level (INT8/FP8);
:Deploy Model to REST/gRPC Endpoint;

|Observability & Compliance|
fork
  :Stream Telemetry to Prometheus/Grafana;
  :Monitor PUE and Thermal Levels;
fork again
  :Log API Access (365-day Retention);
  :Verify Tenant Logical Isolation;
end fork

|AI Engineer / Data Scientist|
:Perform Inference (<50ms Latency);
:Review Resource Utilization Dashboard;

stop
@enduml